EDA do log de eventos

O qu

Como usamos dados derivados dos logs de eventos da wikimedia, aqui primeiro exploramos esses logs para entender como os eventos foram coletados, e para procurar caractersticas inesperadas.

Lendo os eventos

events = read_csv("https://github.com/wikimedia-research/Discovery-Hiring-Analyst-2016/raw/master/events_log.csv.gz")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   uuid = col_character(),
##   timestamp = col_double(),
##   session_id = col_character(),
##   group = col_character(),
##   action = col_character(),
##   checkin = col_double(),
##   page_id = col_character(),
##   n_results = col_double(),
##   result_position = col_double()
## )
events = events %>% slice(1:5e4) # til para testar cdigo em dados pequenos. Comente na hora de process-los para valer.

events = events %>% 
    group_by(session_id) %>% 
    arrange(timestamp) %>% 
    mutate(search_index = cumsum(action == "searchResultPage"), # contador de buscas na sesso.
           date = ymd_hms(timestamp))  %>% 
    ungroup()

por grupo

events %>%
    count(group) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x=group, y=n)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity")

No tempo

events %>% 
    mutate(date = round_date(date, unit = "day")) %>% 
    count(date, group) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = date, y = n, fill = group)) + 
    geom_area()

Por tipo

events %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=action, fill=group)) +
    geom_bar(position = "dodge")

events %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=action, fill=group)) +
    geom_bar(position = "fill")

events %>% 
    mutate(date = round_date(date, unit = "day")) %>% 
    count(date, action) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = date, y = n, fill = action)) + 
    geom_area()

events %>% 
    mutate(date = round_date(date, unit = "day")) %>% 
    count(date, action) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = date, y = n, color = action)) + 
    geom_line() +
    geom_point()

Number of Results

events %>%
    filter(n_results <=20) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=n_results)) +
    geom_bar()

events %>%
    filter(n_results >20) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=n_results)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth = 10)

## Result position

events %>%
    filter(result_position<20) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=result_position)) +
    geom_bar()
